This paper discusses wireless caching techniques and device-to-device (D2D) communication, which are both related to networking and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a caching algorithm, which involves optimization and decision-making, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. Additionally, the algorithm involves selecting pairs of users, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be a relevant category. The paper also discusses the potential changes in system parameters over time, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) may be a relevant category. Finally, the paper mentions throughput and energy efficiency, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) may also be a relevant category.
